shared_text:
New Jersey Department of Education
April 8 at 7:56 PM Â·

Join us every weekday from 9:00 a.m. to 1:00 p.m. on @NJTV for NJTV Learning Live!

Tomorrow, our educators include Mrs. Chante Wilson-Odum from KIPP Thrive Academy; Mrs. Dana Skillman from Paul Robeson Charter School; Ms. Deirdre Fedison from Swimming River School; and Ms. Fatema Sumrein, Faten Sumrein, and Ms. Christine Correia from Linden Public Schools.

If you live in New Jersey, you can stream the broadcast here: njtvonline.org/live

Or find out what channel to tune into here: https://www.njtvonline.org/about/where-to-watch/

And no matter where you live, you can access past episodes here: njtvonline.org/learn

See you tomorrow!

post_text:
***Important Announcement ***

Tomorrow PRCS is holding a fundraiser to support ECHO, the organization that Jo Carolyn, our guest speaker from this week is working for. If students bring in $1 they are able to dress down. Tomorrow March 22, 2019.

Please keep in mind students are prohibited from wearing the following items. If students wear these items parents will be contacted immediately and consequences may follow.

Excessively tight or excessively baggy pants/jeans/shorts/skirts (including tights, leggings, and jeggings worn as pants)

Shorts and skirts above the knee

Midriff/cut off shirts/crop tops and low cut shirts or necklines.

Tank tops

Clothing with direct or implied inappropriate language, gestures, or images

Over sized jewelry and belt buckles

Flip-flop shoes or sandals

See through and /or ripped clothing (no pants or shirts should have any type of frayed or rip in them, only plain jeans or pants will be acceptable, and no cut up shirts)

Happy Thursday!

post_text:
This month we are featuring Ms. Michener our rock star 7th grade reading teacher! Find out why she loves her job and what she wants for her students: "The part of this job that gives me the greatest satisfaction and sense of accomplishment is monitoring student growth and achievement. My kids grow and grow every day, week, month... It's really fun to show them that. Kids should walk out the front door at the end of the day feeling loved and supported. They should leave knowing Ms. Michener will fight with them and for them, no matter what."
-Ms. Michener

post_text:
Ms. Levach is one of the newest members of the PRCS family! She will be teaching special education as well as 7th and 8th grade RELA.

Ms. Levach is from Hamilton, NJ and studied special education and English at TCNJ. When she first applied to college, she wanted to be a writer. However, she soon found her calling with education! Her biggest inspiration is her dad, who has shown her how important it is to be self motivated and have drive to complete anything she sets her mind to. #prcs #staffspotlight
